content.text:
import json

# Load the HAR file
har_file_path = "/mnt/data/pro.houzz.com.har"

with open(har_file_path, "r", encoding="utf-8") as file:
    har_data = json.load(file)

# Extract relevant information
log_entries = har_data.get("log", {}).get("entries", [])

# Display basic statistics
num_entries = len(log_entries)
domains = set()

for entry in log_entries:
    request = entry.get("request", {})
    url = request.get("url", "")
    if url:
        domain = url.split("/")[2]  # Extract domain from URL
        domains.add(domain)

# Summarizing results
har_summary = {
    "Total Requests": num_entries,
    "Unique Domains": len(domains),
    "Domains": list(domains)
}

har_summary
